data.value: When dogs expose their belly, it's often a sign of trust, vulnerability, and submission. Rolling onto their back and exposing their belly is a submissive posture in the canine world, indicating that they acknowledge the dominance or authority of another individual, whether it's another dog or their human caregiver. It's a gesture that demonstrates their trust and affection, as they feel comfortable enough to let their guard down and reveal their most vulnerable area. In some cases, dogs may also expose their belly as an invitation to play or to seek attention and affection from their human companions. Understanding and respecting this gesture can help strengthen the bond between dogs and their owners, fostering a sense of security and mutual respect in the relationship.
